definitions.definition: Any of several North American plane trees, of the genus Platanus , especially Platanus occidentalis ( American sycamore ), distinguished by its mottled bark which flakes off in large irregular masses.
A large British and European species of maple , Acer pseudoplatanus , known in North America as the sycamore maple .
A large tree bearing edible fruit, Ficus sycomorus , allied to the common fig , found in Egypt and Syria .
